ten zu erzeugen, und zweitens, dass es aus diesem Grund prädestiniert ist für eine Theoretisierung mimetischer Strukturen der Kunst im Allgemeinen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMimesis in art. 0aNature in art. 0aStill-life in art. 0aStill-life paintingx17th centuryxEurope. 0aStill-life paintingzEuropey17th century. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook-Paket AV  Kunst 2013z9783110342697oZDB-23-AKU0 cprintz978305006325640uhttps://doi.org/10.1524/978305009535640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783050095356423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783050095356/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-AKUb2013  aZDB-23-GAAc2000d2014